Full Description: CONNECTING CLICKS, BRICKS AND COOL U*tique is defining how bricks connect with clicks and facilitating omni-channel growth…  With a unique patented automated storefront (robotic vending), centralized real time software-driven management, and an engaging consumer experience, U*tique Shop™ combines the best of e-commerce with instant gratification product delivery (e-commerce in a box).  U*tique Shops™ present a highly edited selection of 56 “must-have” premium lifestyle items and assort them adjacent to a large digital sign which can promote via rich media (built-in advertising).  The automated storefront builds recognition without traditional ad spend, and provides a high net profit/low operating cost and low risk distribution option given its mobile format (on wheels).   Most compelling, these automated storefronts are rich sources of data and advertising impact.  Thousands of user sessions are collected and analyzed in each location per month and continue to inform expansion activities.  Users are opting-in for communication from the brand at high rates (via e-receipts – 75% opt in), which drives lead generation, raising recognition of the brand’s activities online and in the physical landscape.  U*tique is building on this momentum by developing an engaging omni-channel consumer experience (automated – web – mobile), that will combine the best of digital commerce with instant gratification product delivery, in addition to centralized real time management through its Portal™ system.   Already U*tique is centrally fulfilling e-commerce orders completed at its automated stores (consumers can order-to-ship at the U*tique). U*tique Shops™ are currently in high profile venues nationwide, including The Cosmopolitan Hotel in Las Vegas, The Palms Casino Resort, and the Hilton Union Square in San Francisco.   U*tique was recently awarded the Best New Airport Retail Concept in North America by ACI, the Gold Innovation Award for Best Store Design by NAMA, and was named to McKinsey’s “Ones to Watch in Retail” report.  The Company was founded in 2007 and was backed by Silicon Valley entrepreneurs, strategic angels and top seed stage VC funds including First Round Capital, Founder Collective and Palomar Ventures.  It is now part of AVT, Inc. as of April 1, 2013 making it a vertically integrated solution (manufacturing to turnkey retail operation).

Description: Wetlands America Trust, Inc (the trust) is a nonprofit organization formed in 1985 to support ducks unlimited.
Full Description: The goal of Wetlands America Trust is to provide specialized financial and philanthropic support to Ducks Unlimited. It's been that way since WAT was created more than 25 years ago, and it will remain the primary focus for decades to come. WAT's principle role is the fiduciary responsibility for DU's endowment and land holdings. WAT is also one of the nation's largest accredited land trusts, holding conservation easements on more than 400,000 acres. Not only has WAT been successful with this charge, the trustees have individually taken up the mantle to introduce DU and conservation programs to their friends, family and colleagues. Three committees lead the day-to-day activities of the Trust. Chaired by Dan Ray, and using the trustees' vast personal and business networks to recruit new hunter-conservationists, the Development Committee undertakes highly individualized and directed fundraising for DU. Past DU President John Tomke chairs the Government Affairs Committee to build strong relationships with policy makers and to educate public officials on policy issues essential to DU's conservation mission, while the Nominating Committee - chaired by Doug Oberhelman - identifies and recommends potential trustees and manages WAT's governance considerations.

Description: Legalmaster is designed for the firm that wants to combine powerful management tools with simplicity of use.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Legalmaster is designed for the firm that wants to combine powerful management tools with simplicity of use. Legalmaster lets you integrate your "back office" financial record-keeping requirements with your "front office" case management needs. Legalmaster is "modular," letting you automate whatever parts of your firm you wish, and add others as you see the need. The financial side of Legalmaster lets you produce bills that satisfy the requirements of your most demanding clients and simultaneously gives you access to the information you need to let you truly manage the business side of your practice. You may determine the productivity of any aspect of your firm using the same information that Legalmaster needs just to print your bills.The full integration of front and back office functions lets you, for example, search for conflicts through the descriptions of every time entry you've ever entered. The case management screens allow you to display vital matter information that the back office billing people have already supplied. The most time-consuming task in a billing system is not, as most people think, the entry of financial transactions. Rather, it's the correcting of entry errors and modification of transactions prior to billing. They have devoted and continue to devote lots of resource to make this aspect of your job as painless and efficient as possible.
